issue.body:
ES3 has no notion of strict mode, and so the following is a valid script:

```js
'use strict';
00;
```

But it results in a `SyntaxError`:

```js
const acorn = require("acorn");

acorn.parse("'use strict';\n00;\n", { ecmaVersion: 3 });
```

Related: https://github.com/eslint/eslint/issues/15456
